definitions.definition: Any of two or more compounds with the same molecular formula but with different structure .
Any of two or more atomic nuclei with the same mass number and atomic number but with different radioactive properties.

main_definition: ( physical chemistry ) Any of two or more compounds with the same molecular formula but with different structure .
secondary_definitions: ( nuclear physics ) Any of two or more atomic nuclei with the same mass number and atomic number but with different radioactive properties.
